Objective: To comprehensively analyze the disease burden of drowning in the 
Chinese population both at the national and provincial levels in 1990 and 2013, 
to provide reference for the development of strategies regarding drowning 
prevention. Methods: Both methods related to unified measurement framework and 
standardized estimation on Global Burden of Disease in 2013, were used. Data on 
deaths caused by injuries were from the following sources which include: Disease 
Surveillance Points, the National Maternal and Child Health Surveillance 
